# Contributing to GPR Utility Detection Tool

Thank you for your interest in contributing! This document provides guidelines for contributing to this project.

## How to Contribute

### Reporting Bugs

Before submitting a bug report:
- Check the [existing issues](https://github.com/yourusername/gpr-utility-detection/issues) to avoid duplicates
- Collect information about the bug:
  - Steps to reproduce
  - Expected behavior
  - Actual behavior
  - GPR data specifications (frequency, samples, etc.)
  - ArcGIS Pro version
  - Python environment details

**Submit bugs via GitHub Issues** with the "bug" label.

### Suggesting Enhancements

Enhancement suggestions are welcome! Please:
- Check existing feature requests first
- Provide clear use cases
- Explain why this feature would benefit users
- Consider implementation complexity

**Submit via GitHub Issues** with the "enhancement" label.

### Pull Requests

1. **Fork the repository** and create your branch from `main`
2. **Make your changes**:
   - Follow existing code style
   - Add comments for complex logic
   - Update documentation if needed
3. **Test thoroughly**:
   - Test with multiple GPR datasets
   - Verify ArcGIS Pro integration
   - Check edge cases
4. **Update the README** if adding features
5. **Submit pull request** with clear description

### Code Style

- Follow PEP 8 for Python code
- Use descriptive variable names
- Add docstrings for functions/classes
- Keep functions focused and modular
- Comment complex algorithms

### Priority Areas for Contribution

**High Priority:**
- Support for additional GPR file formats
- Validation tools and accuracy testing
- Performance optimization
- Better error handling and logging

**Medium Priority:**
- Enhanced visualization options
- Export to additional formats
- Utility type classification
- Integration with other GIS platforms

**Low Priority:**
- UI/UX improvements
- Additional preprocessing options
- Advanced filtering capabilities

### Testing

When contributing code:
- Test with real GPR data
- Include test results in PR
- Document any limitations
- Verify backward compatibility

### Documentation

- Update README.md for user-facing changes
- Add inline code comments
- Update parameter descriptions
- Include usage examples

## Community Guidelines

- Be respectful and constructive
- Help others learn and grow
- Share knowledge and experience
- Acknowledge contributions

## Questions?

- Open a [Discussion](https://github.com/yourusername/gpr-utility-detection/discussions) for general questions
- Use [Issues](https://github.com/yourusername/gpr-utility-detection/issues) for bugs/features
- Contact maintainers directly for sensitive matters

## Recognition

Contributors will be acknowledged in:
- README.md contributors section
- Release notes
- Project documentation

Thank you for helping improve GPR utility detection!
